WEBVTT

00:00:03.279 --> 00:00:06.379
Before our Lord Jesus returned to heaven,

00:00:06.379 --> 00:00:09.980
He gave what has been called the Great Commission.

00:00:09.980 --> 00:00:11.119
He said,

00:00:11.119 --> 00:00:16.019
go there for and make disciples of people of all the nations,

00:00:16.019 --> 00:00:18.820
baptizing them in the name of the Father

00:00:18.820 --> 00:00:22.320
and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit.

00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:26.660
No doubt you have those words in your mind as well.

00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:32.700
Jesus was not satisfied that people should just come to know his teachings.

00:00:32.939 --> 00:00:36.799
Jesus wanted people to come to love his teachings

00:00:36.799 --> 00:00:39.079
so that they would act on them,

00:00:39.079 --> 00:00:41.579
so that they would live by them

00:00:41.579 --> 00:00:45.780
and so that they would become his true disciples.

00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:50.259
Now, why did Jesus want people to become his disciples

00:00:50.259 --> 00:00:52.420
and live by his teachings?

00:00:52.420 --> 00:00:55.219
Well, it's because of something that we read here

00:00:55.219 --> 00:00:58.299
in John chapter 13 and verse 17.

00:00:59.659 --> 00:01:01.380
Now, notice what Jesus said here.

00:01:02.380 --> 00:01:05.500
If you know these things,

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:08.980
happy you are if you do them.

00:01:08.980 --> 00:01:10.620
What's the point?

00:01:10.620 --> 00:01:15.260
Jesus was saying that people would find real happiness.

00:01:15.260 --> 00:01:17.700
They would find the way of salvation.

00:01:17.700 --> 00:01:21.900
They would have a relationship with his precious Heavenly Father

00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:27.700
if they would just come to know and do the things that he had taught.

00:01:27.700 --> 00:01:30.500
Well, brothers and sisters, in this symposium,

00:01:30.540 --> 00:01:33.980
we are going to discuss five different things

00:01:33.980 --> 00:01:36.540
that our Bible students need to do,

00:01:36.540 --> 00:01:38.579
that they need to progress in

00:01:38.579 --> 00:01:43.700
if they are going to become true disciples of our Lord Jesus Christ.

00:01:43.700 --> 00:01:46.060
Let's talk about the first.

00:01:46.060 --> 00:01:51.140
What is the most basic need that our Bible students have?

00:01:51.140 --> 00:01:55.340
Well, it's what Jesus talked about here in Matthew chapter 5.

00:01:55.340 --> 00:01:56.500
Let's read it together.

00:01:57.500 --> 00:02:01.099
Matthew chapter 5 and verse 3.

00:02:02.579 --> 00:02:07.379
Jesus said, happy are those conscious of their notice?

00:02:07.379 --> 00:02:12.379
Spiritual need since the kingdom of the heavens belongs to them.

00:02:13.460 --> 00:02:15.020
What's the point?

00:02:15.020 --> 00:02:20.020
Well, Jesus showed that honest-hearted people have a spiritual need.

00:02:20.939 --> 00:02:23.379
They have a need to come to know God

00:02:23.379 --> 00:02:25.419
and to have a relationship with him.

00:02:25.460 --> 00:02:28.460
If they're really going to be happy.

00:02:28.460 --> 00:02:34.460
Therefore, we need to teach our Bible students the very first thing

00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:38.580
to see how they can fill that spiritual need

00:02:38.580 --> 00:02:42.419
by learning about their Heavenly Father, Jehovah.

00:02:42.419 --> 00:02:44.060
As they fill that need,

00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:46.900
as they come to have that relationship with God,

00:02:46.900 --> 00:02:49.419
that is the way to true happiness.

00:02:50.419 --> 00:02:55.180
That means more than just feeding people information.

00:02:55.219 --> 00:02:58.379
You know, there's a saying that's very familiar to most of us.

00:02:58.379 --> 00:03:02.780
It says, give a man a fish, feed him for a day.

00:03:02.780 --> 00:03:06.900
Teach him how to fish, feed him for a lifetime.

00:03:06.900 --> 00:03:08.580
What's the point?

00:03:08.580 --> 00:03:13.860
If we can teach our Bible students how to feed themselves spiritually,

00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:16.460
then they have the way in front of them

00:03:16.460 --> 00:03:18.860
to a close relationship with God,

00:03:18.860 --> 00:03:23.860
to strong faith and becoming real disciples of Jesus Christ.

00:03:24.860 --> 00:03:28.740
Well, now in the following demonstration that you'll see on video,

00:03:28.740 --> 00:03:53.280
just notice how our Bible teacher helps her student to be able to do this.

00:03:53.280 --> 00:03:54.879
Got it.

00:03:55.879 --> 00:03:57.879
I find the answers in all that.

