Because of what need to call meditation,

00:05:26.199 --> 00:05:30.399
it's not about clearing your mind to find inner peace.

00:05:30.399 --> 00:05:32.000
It's totally different.

00:05:32.959 --> 00:05:37.720
It's asking how Jehovah feels about something.

00:05:37.720 --> 00:05:48.170
And then what that means for me.

00:05:48.170 --> 00:05:50.649
Now, what did you notice in the video?

00:05:50.649 --> 00:05:54.170
It's true, Nita showed her Bible student the tools.

00:05:54.170 --> 00:05:57.170
But what more did she do?

00:05:57.170 --> 00:06:00.329
She also helped her to see that the answers

00:06:00.329 --> 00:06:02.129
were not the most important thing.

00:06:02.129 --> 00:06:05.209
The most important thing was having the information

00:06:05.209 --> 00:06:08.370
come to touch her heart so that she would be moved

00:06:08.490 --> 00:06:10.810
to act on what she learned.

00:06:11.730 --> 00:06:13.850
Well, how can we help our students

00:06:13.850 --> 00:06:17.529
to be able to feed themselves spiritually?

00:06:17.529 --> 00:06:18.689
Well, from the very beginning,

00:06:18.689 --> 00:06:20.970
once the study has been established,

00:06:20.970 --> 00:06:24.209
we want to teach our students how to prepare

00:06:24.209 --> 00:06:26.209
each week for the study.

00:06:26.209 --> 00:06:28.569
Now, this might be something very new to them.

00:06:28.569 --> 00:06:30.089
So we're going to have to go through it

00:06:30.089 --> 00:06:33.569
step by step showing them how to prepare.

00:06:33.569 --> 00:06:36.410
It might also involve having to help them see

00:06:36.410 --> 00:06:39.329
how they can buy out time from their schedule

00:06:39.329 --> 00:06:43.730
so that they can do what's necessary to prepare.

00:06:43.730 --> 00:06:46.050
And then don't forget to commend them

00:06:46.050 --> 00:06:49.329
because this might be very new for many of our students

00:06:49.329 --> 00:06:51.329
when they make the effort to prepare,

00:06:51.329 --> 00:06:53.569
make sure you give appropriate commendation.

00:06:54.810 --> 00:06:57.089
But then what's the next thing?

00:06:57.089 --> 00:07:00.170
This is something that we sometimes forget, brothers.

00:07:00.170 --> 00:07:03.329
It's the need to teach our students to pray

00:07:03.410 --> 00:07:06.410
before every single study session.

00:07:06.410 --> 00:07:08.769
Now, why is this important?

00:07:08.769 --> 00:07:11.569
Well, once again, we want our students

00:07:11.569 --> 00:07:16.009
not just to be thinking in terms of acquiring information

00:07:16.009 --> 00:07:20.050
to not take an academic approach to their study,

00:07:20.050 --> 00:07:22.769
but instead be always thinking about

00:07:22.769 --> 00:07:25.850
how what they're studying connects them

00:07:25.850 --> 00:07:28.290
with their Heavenly Father Jehovah

00:07:28.290 --> 00:07:32.490
so that they're building up a relationship with him

00:07:32.529 --> 00:07:34.930
as Proverbs chapter two says,

00:07:34.930 --> 00:07:37.730
if we call out to Jehovah for knowledge,

00:07:37.730 --> 00:07:40.529
for wisdom, for understanding,

00:07:40.529 --> 00:07:42.250
Jehovah will help us.

00:07:42.250 --> 00:07:44.970
He'll help our student to gain that knowledge

00:07:44.970 --> 00:07:48.889
that they need to build up a good relationship with him.

00:07:48.889 --> 00:07:51.649
And then we want to do practical things.

00:07:51.649 --> 00:07:54.610
We want to help our students to become familiar

00:07:54.610 --> 00:07:58.930
with the digital tools that we have at our disposal for study.

00:07:58.930 --> 00:08:01.170
That means helping them to install

00:08:01.170 --> 00:08:03.529
on their phone, on their tablet,

00:08:03.529 --> 00:08:07.129
or whatever device they have, JW Library,

00:08:07.129 --> 00:08:10.810
showing them how to use Watchtower Online Library

00:08:10.810 --> 00:08:13.449
so that they can get the answers that they need

00:08:13.449 --> 00:08:14.810
to their questions.

